.TH EDGESHIELD 8 "2026-07-19" "0.1.0" "EdgeShield Manual"
.SH NAME
edgeshield \- lightweight network security monitoring daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B edgeshield
[\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-\-version\fR]
.B edgeshield run
[\fB\-c\fR \fIconfig\fR]
.B edgeshield default-config
.B edgeshield setup
[\fIoptions\fR]
.B edgeshield tui
[\fIoptions\fR]
.B edgeshield completions
\fIshell\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
EdgeShield is a lightweight, self-hosted network behavior monitoring daemon
designed for Raspberry Pi, homelabs, and small businesses. It captures packets
on a network interface, identifies devices by MAC/IP, tracks protocols, and
exposes the device inventory over a REST API.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B run
Start the EdgeShield daemon.
.TP
.B default-config
Print the default TOML configuration to stdout.
.TP
.B setup
First-run setup wizard. Generates a TOML config file, either
interactively (prompting for each setting) or non-interactively (from
flags). Can optionally generate an API key and wire up a notifier
(MQTT, ntfy, webhook, or email). In non-interactive mode, required
values must come from flags.
.RS
.B Options:
.RS
\fB\-\-config\fR=\fIPATH\fR    Path to write (default: /etc/edgeshield/config.toml)
.br
\fB\-\-non-interactive\fR  Run without prompting
.br
\fB\-\-force\fR            Overwrite an existing config
.br
\fB\-\-interface\fR=\fINAME\fR  Network interface to capture
.br
\fB\-\-api-port\fR=\fIPORT\fR   REST API port (default: 8080)
.br
\fB\-\-bind\fR=\fIADDR\fR       Bind address (default: 0.0.0.0)
.br
\fB\-\-database-path\fR=\fIPATH\fR  SQLite path (empty = in-memory)
.br
\fB\-\-generate-api-key\fR  Generate a random API key
.br
\fB\-\-enable-mqtt\fR / \fB\-\-enable-ntfy\fR / \fB\-\-enable-webhook\fR / \fB\-\-enable-email\fR
Enable a notification channel (with corresponding \-\-mqtt-host, \-\-ntfy-url, etc.)
.RE
.TP
.B tui
Launch the read-only terminal UI dashboard. Connects to a running
daemon over its REST API.
.TP
.B completions \fIshell\fR
Print a shell completion script (bash or zsh).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-c ", " \-\-config "=" path
Path to the TOML configuration file (default: /etc/edgeshield/config.toml).
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is read from a TOML file. The default path is
\fI/etc/edgeshield/config.toml\fR. Fallback paths include
\fI/usr/local/etc/edgeshield/config.toml\fR, \fI./edgeshield.toml\fR,
and \fI./config.toml\fR.
.P
Example configuration:
.P
.RS
.nf
interface = "eth0"
api_port = 8080
log_level = "info"
capture_buffer = 4096
.RE
.SH ENDPOINTS
.TP
.B GET /health
Returns {"status":"ok","version":"0.1.0"}.
.TP
.B GET /devices
Returns the full device inventory as a JSON array.
.TP
.B GET /devices/{mac}
Returns a single device by MAC address (e.g., 00:11:22:33:44:55).
.TP
.B GET /metrics
Returns aggregate metrics (device count, packet count, byte count, uptime).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/edgeshield/config.toml
Default configuration file.
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGINT, SIGTERM
Graceful shutdown.
.TP
.B SIGHUP
Reload configuration (future).
.SH REQUIREMENTS
Packet capture requires root privileges or the CAP_NET_RAW capability:
.RS
.nf
sudo setcap cap_net_raw+ep $(which edgeshield)
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tcpdump (8),
.BR systemd.service (5)
.SH AUTHOR
EdgeShield Contributors
